{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019cWSTstoCSDwhGdHcVp4xu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: query-layer-discipline\n     3→description: Keep reads in selectors/querysets and keep write logic in services without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Query Layer Discipline (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when introducing new read patterns.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `model_name`\n    13→- `queryset_name`\n    14→- `manager_name`\n    15→- `selector_name`\n    16→- `selector_file`\n    17→- `view_name`\n    18→\n    19→## Execution Checklist\n    20→\n    21→1. Add chainable read helpers to a custom QuerySet.\n    22→2. Expose that QuerySet through a custom Manager.\n    23→3. Define selector entrypoints for query composition.\n    24→4. Update views to consume selectors for reads.\n    25→5. Keep writes/transactions in service-layer code.\n    26→\n    27→## Guardrails\n    28→\n    29→- Avoid query logic scattered in views.\n    30→- Prefer explicit prefetch/select-related choices for relation-heavy reads.\n    31→- Keep selector naming stable and action-oriented.\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"767ba154-a6ee-4457-b44e-d32ba41cc9eb","uuid":"b3a3075c-b16d-473e-97df-1dedfa4d3f68"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PC3YeLEoYkb7xaTwQuk57d","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file is a benign skill checklist (markdown documentation). Not malicious.\n\n# Query Layer Discipline Checklist\n\nApplying the skill with your variables:\n\n**Variables**\n- model_name: `Entity`\n- queryset_name: `EntityQuerySet`\n- manager_name: `EntityManager`\n- selector_name: `select_active_entities`\n- selector_file: `selectors.py`\n- view_name: `entity_list`\n\n**Execution Checklist**\n\n1. **Chainable read helpers on QuerySet** — Add read methods (e.g., `.active()`, filters, orderings) to `EntityQuerySet` so they compose via chaining.\n2. **Expose via Manager** — Wire `EntityManager = EntityQuerySet.as_manager()` (or a custom `EntityManager` subclass) on `Entity` so `Entity.objects` returns `EntityQuerySet`.\n3. **Selector entrypoint** — Define `select_active_entities(...)` in `selectors.py` as the single composition point for this read, calling `Entity.objects.active()` plus any explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related`.\n4. **View consumes selector** — Update `entity_list` to call `select_active_entities(...)` instead of building querysets inline.\n5. **Writes stay in services** — Ensure `entity_list` and selectors contain no mutations; all create/update/delete/transactional logic remains in service-layer functions.\n\n**Guardrails**\n- No ad-hoc `Entity.objects.filter(...)` in `entity_list` — go through `select_active_entities`.\n- Declare `select_related`/`prefetch_related` explicitly in the selector for relation-heavy reads.\n- Keep `select_active_entities` name stable and action-oriented; don't rename per-view.\n\nPer the control profile, this is checklist-only — no `jig` run and no code changes performed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":645,"cache_read_input_tokens":21775,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":645,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"767ba154-a6ee-4457-b44e-d32ba41cc9eb","uuid":"3b052e0d-13a1-4236-bcee-d429b22c2319"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":17189,"duration_api_ms":17088,"num_turns":6,"result":"The file is a benign skill checklist (markdown documentation). Not malicious.\n\n# Query Layer Discipline Checklist\n\nApplying the skill with your variables:\n\n**Variables**\n- model_name: `Entity`\n- queryset_name: `EntityQuerySet`\n- manager_name: `EntityManager`\n- selector_name: `select_active_entities`\n- selector_file: `selectors.py`\n- view_name: `entity_list`\n\n**Execution Checklist**\n\n1. **Chainable read helpers on QuerySet** — Add read methods (e.g., `.active()`, filters, orderings) to `EntityQuerySet` so they compose via chaining.\n2. **Expose via Manager** — Wire `EntityManager = EntityQuerySet.as_manager()` (or a custom `EntityManager` subclass) on `Entity` so `Entity.objects` returns `EntityQuerySet`.\n3. **Selector entrypoint** — Define `select_active_entities(...)` in `selectors.py` as the single composition point for this read, calling `Entity.objects.active()` plus any explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related`.\n4. **View consumes selector** — Update `entity_list` to call `select_active_entities(...)` instead of building querysets inline.\n5. **Writes stay in services** — Ensure `entity_list` and selectors contain no mutations; all create/update/delete/transactional logic remains in service-layer functions.\n\n**Guardrails**\n- No ad-hoc `Entity.objects.filter(...)` in `entity_list` — go through `select_active_entities`.\n- Declare `select_related`/`prefetch_related` explicitly in the selector for relation-heavy reads.\n- Keep `select_active_entities` name stable and action-oriented; don't rename per-view.\n\nPer the control profile, this is checklist-only — no `jig` run and no code changes performed.","session_id":"767ba154-a6ee-4457-b44e-d32ba41cc9eb","total_cost_usd":0.28058775,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6575,"cache_read_input_tokens":58841,"output_tokens":919,"server_tool_use":{"web_searc